title: For Sale:  Remington, Model 8, 25 cal
postcontent:
The model 8 was manufactured from 1911-1936 and 80500 made.  This serial number in mid 15k.  

The Remington Model 8 rifle is long recoil-operated and uses a rotating bolt head. After firing, the barrel and bolt, still locked together, move rearward inside the receiver and compress two recoil springs. Then the bolt is held back while the barrel is returned forward by one of the springs permitting extraction and ejection. Once the barrel is returned, the bolt is returned forward by the second spring; in so doing it picks up a fresh round from the magazine and chambers it. The Remington Model 8 has a fixed 5-shot magazine and bolt hold-open device which engages after the magazine is empty.

title: For Sale:  M1 Carbine - Standard Products
postcontent:
Selling my extra USGI M1 Carbines. These are a great piece of our history and a very fun firearm to shoot. After shooting one you see why they were so popular by our troops in WWII.

The IBM has an original IBM barrel and a good deal of IBM parts. Would take minimal effort to make 100% correct. Selling it for $950. (SOLD)

The Standard Quality has an Underwood barrel and is correct for this manufacturer. Standard did not make their own barrels and was part of what was called the free barrel program. The wood on this is very nice. Selling it for $950. The three phots below have been updated to be all of the Standard carbine.

Of the 5.5 million or so of these made (who really knows how many remain after war loss, US governemnt destroying these with captain crunch and the large number given to our allies)IBM and Standard were of the most rare. Standard made only about 247 thousand and IBM made only about 346 thousand.

Both are from the CMP, and I will include the paperwork and documentation. If you want magazines or ammo, I will sell as part of package for reasonable (at cost) price. USGI 15 rd magazines (will try to make match rifle manufacturer) for $20 each. 30 rd magazines for $22 each. 50 rounds of carbine ammo for either $25 a box (Aquila) or $30 for Lake CIty. I may even have a M4 bayonet or two if interested.

I will be posting photos this afternoon, just wanted to get these listed ASAP because I want to move these this weekend and the prices reflect that for nearly correct carbines. Frankly I was not planning on selling but the new laws have me concerned that when I liquidate my collection it is going to be a pain in the a$$. I will also have additional photos upon request.

FTF only and thank you for looking. If these do not sell this weekend, I will consider shipping but first priority for expediency and to provide last opportunity to buy one without government meddling is face to face in Colorado
